-- GMP Names Wright Chairman as Beck Retires From Board
-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 2012-04-12T13:33:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/gmp-names-wright-chairman-as-beck-retires-from-board-1-.html
GMP Capital Inc. (GMP) , Canada’s second-
biggest independent brokerage, plans to appoint Donald A. Wright
chairman after its annual  shareholders’ meeting  next month.  Wright, a former president of Merrill Lynch Canada and
chief executive officer of  Toronto-Dominion Bank (TD) ’s TD
Securities, has been on GMP’s board since 2004, the Toronto-
based company said today in a statement.  Stanley M. Beck will retire from the board May 4, the day
of GMP’s annual meeting, after serving more than eight years as
chairman, the company said.  Canaccord Financial Inc. (CF)  is the country’s biggest
independent brokerage by assets.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scheer at 
 dscheer@bloomberg.net  